<HEADLINE>
Football: Cardiff to face Portsmouth in FA Cup final
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cardiff City will play Portsmouth in this season's FA Cup final
after beating fellow Championship side Barnsley 1-0 in Sunday's
second semi-final here at Wembley.
</P>
<P>
Joe Ledley's ninth minute goal saw Cardiff, the only non-English
side to lift the FA Cup when they beat Arsenal 1-0 back in 1927,
into the May 17 final at Wembley.
</P>
<P>
Portsmouth, the last Premier League side left in this season's FA
Cup, beat West Bromwich Albion, also of the second-tier
Championship, by the same scoreline in Saturday's first semi-
final at Wembley, thanks to a goal from former Baggies striker
Nwankwo Kanu.
</P>
